<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lop2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lop,</orth> vb. 1) to cut off, as branches from trees: <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 6, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.454" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 454</bibl>. Used of limbs: <bibl n="shak. tit 1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 143</bibl>. <cit><quote>to l. that doubt,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 90</bibl></cit>. With <cit><quote>away:</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.64" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 4, 64</bibl></cit>. with <cit><quote>off:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 1, 43</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 3, 42</bibl>.<lb />2) to shorten by cutting off the branches: <cit><quote>have --ed and hewed and made thy body bare of her two branches,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 4, 17</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>